#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:3
msgid "Building packages for Pyodide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:5
msgid ""
"This document describes how to build packages for Pyodide. It is intended "
"for package maintainers and developers who want to build packages for "
"Pyodide or add packages to the Pyodide distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:9
msgid "Determining if building a package is necessary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:11
msgid ""
"Before starting to build packages for Pyodide, please check if it is "
"necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:13
msgid ""
"If the package is a pure Python package and does not use any native "
"extensions such as C, Cython, or Rust, it is likely to work with Pyodide "
"without building it. In that case, try installing it from PyPI with {func}"
"`micropip.install` in Pyodide. Try `await micropip.install(\"package-"
"name\")` to see if it works."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:18
msgid ""
"There are packages already built for Pyodide and included in the Pyodide "
"distribution. Visit [`pyodide-recipes`](https://github.com/pyodide/pyodide-"
"recipes) repository to see if the package you need is already built and "
"available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:22
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:24
msgid ""
"Pyodide currently only supports building packages in Linux environments "
"officially, though there is a good chance it will work in MacOS too. If you "
"are using Windows, try Windows Subsystem for Linux."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:28
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:30
msgid "Prepare proper host Python version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:32
msgid ""
"Before starting to build packages for Pyodide, you need to have a host "
"Python version that is compatible with the target Pyodide version. For "
"example, if you want to build packages for Pyodide 0.27.5, which contains "
"Python 3.12.7, you need Python 3.12 installed on your host system. Using "
"different Python versions will result in build errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:37
msgid "Install `pyodide-build`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:39
msgid ""
"`pyodide-build` is a build tool for cross-compiling packages for Pyodidde. "
"You can install it using pip:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:41
msgid "pip install pyodide-build\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:45
msgid ""
"After installation, `pyodide` command will be available in your shell. If "
"not, pip might have installed it in a local directory. Please check the "
"installation directory and add it to your PATH."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:48
msgid "Install the build toolchain for target Pyodide:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:50
msgid "pyodide xbuildenv install <target-pyodide-version>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:54
msgid ""
"This command will fail if the host Python version is not compatible with the "
"target Pyodide version. In that case, run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:57
msgid "pyodide xbuildenv search -a\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:61
msgid ""
"to find the compatible Python version and update the local Python version to "
"match the target Pyodide version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:63
msgid "Setup [Emscripten](https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:65
msgid ""
"Emscripten is a compiler toolchain for compiling native code to WebAssembly. "
"You need to download and activate the Emscripten version that matches the "
"target Pyodide version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:68
msgid ""
"git clone https://github.com/emscripten-core/emsdk\n"
"cd emsdk\n"
"\n"
"PYODIDE_EMSCRIPTEN_VERSION=$(pyodide config get emscripten_version)\n"
"./emsdk install ${PYODIDE_EMSCRIPTEN_VERSION}\n"
"./emsdk activate ${PYODIDE_EMSCRIPTEN_VERSION}\n"
"source emsdk_env.sh\n"
"which emcc\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:79
msgid ""
"Running `source emsdk_env.sh` will set up the environment variables needed "
"for Emscripten. If you restart your shell, you need to run `source emsdk_env."
"sh` again to set up the environment variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/building-packages.md:82
msgid "Now you are ready to build packages for Pyodide."
msgstr ""

